reviewText: My 18 month old loves this DVD. She watches is at least once a day, if not more.
Was not pleased with the new Mickey Mouse clubhouse. I buy all the DVDs for my daughter and three of the episodes are repeats from other DVDs.

My girls love Mickey Mouse Clubhouse. This DVD contains five episodes from the Disney Jr. cartoon. Amazon doesn't always do a good job on their DVD episode listings so here are the episodes that are included on this DVD:

1. Minnie's Pet Salon - The friends prepare for Pluto's All-Star Pet Show.
2. Daisy's Pet Project - Daisy has to choose a pet for the Pet Parade.
3. Pluto's Puppy-Sitting Adventure - Mickey puppy-sits Clarabelle's puppy, Bella.
4. Donald's Ducks - Donald helps some ducks get to the beach.
5. Pluto Lends a Paw - Minnie's cat Figaro is missing and Mickey and Pluto help find him.
Nice

I bought this DVD for my daughter to watch on a road trip and it has become a staple in our daily playtime activities. She loves Minnie Mouse and animals (especially kitties) so this was a great combo of both. I highly suggest this for anyone in your family who loves the Mickey Mouse clubhouse and specifically the Minnie Mouse focused episodes.

I got this because my child discovered Mickey and Minnie, as they are branded on everything, and really likes the animated Christmas stories. I didn't know until seeing this that Disney makes crap. The CG looks like it's from 2000 and the production value is low.
The episodes are all the same and run together so you can't tell them apart. For a parent it's annoying as these little jingles and sayings get stuck in your head. And for some reason Mickey uses names that sound like Iron Curtain code names, Miska, Moska, and Mooseka, such as the kitten names from the pet store and his code to start the show or whatever Mickey is doing when he chants this. Not sure what it means.
It's so bright though and the characters bounce and bob in a hypnotic way that it seems to really captive kids. The shows are designed as if the kids will interact with it but they do not. They all sort of sit there with blank expressions staring and I'm expecting drool at any moment. I'm including this with my experience of my nieces and nephews watching it. This show is so much dumber than anything else my child is interested in. If you want your kids distracted enough so you can do something uninterrupted this is for you. But it may also temporarily lower their IQ. And have other annoying and unintended side effects.
